Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.07,0:09:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Tsumagari of room 503.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.97,0:09:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's about that thing, I'm sure my\Nhusband already refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.67,0:09:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but I just can't give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.01,0:09:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I brought an appraiser with me today,\Nand I thought I'd ask him one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.65,0:09:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, please
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.15,0:09:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is really something
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.59,0:09:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,his is a fine Hina doll set
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A famous doll craftsman in\NKyoto seems to have made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How much will you sell it to me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.97,0:09:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you buying these dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.14,0:09:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too late, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.07,0:09:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were already given to Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.44,0:10:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't have a daughter so\NI'm not interested in dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.55,0:10:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I want her to sell me is the\Nhanging scroll behind all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Thunder God\Nthat was drawn by
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.52,0:10:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,an artist of the Edo era\Nnamed Tetsuyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.72,0:10:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have the Wind God which is the\Nother half of this hanging scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.69,0:10:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I really want to make\Nit a complete set.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.23,0:10:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, my husband says he has\Nno intention of selling it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and besides, it doesn't\NIook to be something so valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know?\NHow valuable that hanging scroll is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.01,0:10:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea\Nhow much insurance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your husband's late\Nfather placed on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.41,0:10:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.45,0:10:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,20,000,000 yen, 20,000,000 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.08,0:10:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That much?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.28,0:10:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told your husband that I would\Npay him double that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.52,0:10:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I feel\Nsorry for this hanging scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.54,0:10:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If kept in this manner, the value\Nof this scroll will go down
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it'd be wiser to sell it to a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,professional collector like\NMr. Tsumagari.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.33,0:10:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We will not sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how much\Nmoney you dish out for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.21,0:11:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.74,0:11:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'll be back again tonight just\Nabout the time your husband comes home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.18,0:11:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll agree to sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.82,0:11:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I mention the story about him\Nmaking a great loss in stocks
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's put away the dolls and\Nhurry on home too, then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How nostalgic, it's already been\N10 years since we last decorated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.74,0:11:36.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dolls look happy that they were
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,taken out of the box\Nafter such a long time too
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.64,0:11:40.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.31,0:11:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi, would it be okay to decorate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.32,0:11:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,these dolls here\Nuntil Girls' Day Festival this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess mother wants to\Nsay goodbye to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!\NBut, can I stay here a while longer then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.09,0:11:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I have one more\Npicture I want to take...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.90,0:12:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you have mother serve\Nyou some sweet sake then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.67,0:12:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought we were out of the ingredients\Nto make it from scratch?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.21,0:12:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to go out soon too
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.31,0:12:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go buy it then!\NThe supermarket is right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.45,0:12:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi, isn't it about time you tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.05,0:12:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what do you\Nwant to take a picture of?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.17,0:12:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what do you\Nwant to take a picture of?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.42,0:12:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what do you\Nwant to take a Ricture of?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A picture of all of us having a good time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.51,0:12:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just took one like\Nthat a while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just took one like\Nthat a while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.96,0:12:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.30,0:12:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which way was it? \
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.97,0:12:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.94,0:12:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, just a little while more to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.48,0:12:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.61,0:12:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was just around this corner...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.28,0:12:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the appraiser?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.52,0:12:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you went home?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:13:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I forgot my cell phone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called my cell phone, then the lady
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,answered and told\Nme that it's in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me I could get\Nit when I go over tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.63,0:13:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I may get important phone calls so
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.30,0:13:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I decided toe pick it up now.\NBut, it seems that no one's home...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.64,0:13:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean grandma isn't home?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.55,0:13:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's right, nobody's home...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.92,0:13:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NO one is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.66,0:13:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. the door's not locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if grandma went to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.57,0:13:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.14,0:13:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's the sound of the fax machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.54,0:13:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's coming from this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.64,0:13:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is going on!\NThe room is super messed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.29,0:14:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fax seems-to be from her husband
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.92,0:14:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't seem to be the only place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.63,0:14:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Burglary. A burglar\Nbroke in after we left
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.27,0:14:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the looks of it, maybe the\Nother rooms are messed up as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.34,0:14:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.74,0:14:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.14,0:14:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.01,0:14:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad the dolls are fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:29.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room looks untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.65,0:14:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder where grandma is, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.12,0:14:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that grandma's not the\Nonly one who disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.06,0:14:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.49,0:14:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hanging scroll of the\NThunder God is gone too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.20,0:14:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's call the police right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.90,0:14:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G,Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:14:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so I did miss you, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.25,0:15:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, when I looked I\Nfound out that I had also run
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.05,0:15:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,out of sugar, so I went to buy some.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.98,0:15:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, why are you all\NIooking pale faced about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W. Well, the thing is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.99,0:15:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Setsuko, I thought you went out...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.53,0:15:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot my wallet so\NI came back to get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.33,0:15:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bedroom's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.63,0:15:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.83,0:15:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. so we were just\Nabout to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.80,0:15:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Iv.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.67,0:15:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M.Mr. Tsumagari!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.08,0:15:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?\NI heard somebody scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.35,0:15:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, the thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.38,0:15:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A burglar, a burglar broke in .
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.28,0:15:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's talk after the police get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so from what a gather here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.16,0:15:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,those children came here to decorate\Nthe Hina dolls; and after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.16,0:15:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tsumagari who extremely-wanted\Nthe hanging scroll thatflwas stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.27,0:15:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,brought appraiser, Mr. Mie with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.24,0:16:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer, please don't say it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after the two men left,\Nyou five went out shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.31,0:16:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. to buy the ingredients\Nfor making sweet sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.72,0:16:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ingredients for sweet sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.22,0:16:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother was going to make\Nsweet sake for everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.25,0:16:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I realized that we were out\Nof the necessary ingredients
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I had to go out,\NI asked the children to go get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.29,0:16:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that you were here alone,\NGrandma Yayoi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.86,0:16:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you notice anything then?\NLike strange noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.34,0:16:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was quiet, until the cell phone that\Nhe forgot in the living room rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.88,0:16:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y.Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.51,0:16:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you forgot your cell\Nphone in the living room?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were shown into the living room first,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.32,0:16:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because the children\Nwere in the Japanese room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.52,0:16:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we wanted to see the\Nhanging scroll as soon as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.32,0:16:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so forced our way immediately\Ninto the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.63,0:17:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, after the phone call you seem to\Nhave gone out shopping too, but for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went out to buy sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.60,0:17:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized that we were out of\Nsugar so I rushed out to get some.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know about\Nwhat time it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was right after I hung up so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.78,0:17:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, can tell what time it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.95,0:17:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before I hung up. I heard the sound\Nof the FAX on the other side of the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.41,0:17:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so if we look at the time the FAX was\Nsent, we can find out what time it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.16,0:17:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was the FAX from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.90,0:17:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was from my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where is that original FAX?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.97,0:17:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My gosh, they really went all out\Nmessing up the room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.38,0:17:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the FAX\Nyou received from your husband
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.35,0:17:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,3:218 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.55,0:17:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What else was stolen\Nbesides the hangingrscroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:18:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Only hererand the\Nbedroom were ransacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.86,0:18:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the wallet that was on the shelf\Nabove the TV was left untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.73,0:18:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I have a minute\Nwith you, Officer Momose?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.80,0:18:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the burglar broke in\Nfrom the veranda facing this window,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.54,0:18:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.71,0:18:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that this is\Nthe way the burglar broke in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.58,0:18:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're on the 6th floor, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.44,0:18:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a common target for burglars who\Nuse a rope to get down from the roof
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.22,0:18:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They seem to think that people living on\Nthe top floor of condos are rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and most times the windows\Naren't locked anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure know a lot, don't you Au!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.66,0:18:38.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, because ll live with an old man\Nwho likes to watch wide shows on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.70,0:18:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, you're the first ones
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.70,0:18:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who realized that the\Nroom was ransacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.84,0:18:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, when we got back from\Nshopping the front door was unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when we heard the sound of the FAX\Nmachine and came into the living-room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.44,0:18:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all messed up! At that time\Nthe clock on the FAX was 15:40!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.98,0:19:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the\Nburglary took place between
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,15:30 and 15:40 a\Nperiod of 10 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.22,0:19:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.52,0:19:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burglar went down on the veranda\Nand came in through thatswindow, rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.69,0:19:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were me,\NI'd be tooascared to come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you close the window, nothing is in view\Nfrom the veranda because of the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F the burglar opens the window\Nwanting to look inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the curtain would flutter in the wind,\Nand the lady on the phone would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.01,0:19:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, besides the time thezEAX\Nwas sent out all show 15728!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.45,0:19:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the FAX kept coming
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.62,0:19:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in all-the while we were out shopping\Nuntil we came back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.29,0:19:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think a burglar would break
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.26,0:19:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,into airoom where noise is\Nconstantly coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.30,0:19:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it's just the sound of the FAX...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.47,0:19:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The more so frightening\Nbecause it s the FAX!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if the FAX completes\Ncoming in and the buzzer sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.21,0:19:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,somebody in the house\Nmay come to take a look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.94,0:19:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.54,0:20:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beside, it's strange that the burglar\Ndidn't notice her wallet and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.98,0:20:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if the burglar couldn't\Nfind what he was after,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wouldn't all the other rooms\Nbe ransacked too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.72,0:20:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strangest thing is, why only\Nthe hanging scroll was stolen .
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.16,0:20:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that hanging scroll is\Nworth 20:000,000 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fool, only a professional would know\Nif that scroll is really worth that price
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.07,0:20:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the burglar knew\Nthat the scroll was here to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.54,0:20:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,«> <O »\NYeah, but if the burglar\Nwas after the scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.31,0:20:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\ = 49 . wed Pp\NYeah, but if the burglar\Nwas after the scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\Q- fl)\Nthe other room wouldn't\Nhave beenyransacked
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.28,0:20:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the burglar messed up the\Nother room just to throw people off,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.09,0:20:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that he's not suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.04,0:20:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the culprit has no\Ndefinite alibi and on top of that had to face
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.49,0:20:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the police reluctantly after the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.71,0:20:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, that person knows the\Nvalue of that hanging scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.70,0:21:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,\Nyou were loitering -around
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.90,0:21:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in front of this house, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.41,0:21:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,LI just told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.54,0:21:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I came to get my cell phone,\Nbut nobody was home
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.04,0:21:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the door wasn't locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.65,0:21:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you lock the door\Nwhen you left the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.28,0:21:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I think I did,\Nbut I was in a rush so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.66,0:21:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way. whyawere you at the\Nfront door a while ago, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.33,0:21:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came to check things out because\NMr. Mie didn't come back for some time. #
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.27,0:21:30.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you all here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.37,0:21:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he also knew that you\Nforgot your cell phone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.14,0:21:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.34,0:21:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he did, since he was by me until\N@ I started talking to grandma
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.25,0:21:44.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you left\Nwhile he was on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.08,0:21:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,LI just went to buygsome cigarettes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.05,0:21:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, just as this child just said,\Nyou two do not have an alibi yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, will you cut\Nout just suspecting us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.93,0:22:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two are going to get 20,000,000\Nyen too if insurance money comes in!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying that even you two\Ncan carry out something like this!
